result.description:
The 6 yard skip is Ideal for both larger building and refurbishment projects. Also popular for domestic use, house clearances.

Types of waste available for this skip:
o Heavy Waste, Light Waste, Garden, Mixed Building Waste, Mixed Domestic

Waste that cannot be put in a skip:
o TVs/monitors, Plasterboard, Asbestos, Batteries, Tyres, Medical Waste, Flo tubes, Gas cylinders, Electricals, Solvents, Paint tins, Fuels
o Insulation containing asbestos, other insulation containing hazardous substances,other construction materials containing asbestos

The 8 yard skip, also known as the ‘Builders Skip’, is the most common skip used for heavy duty waste such as rubble, soil and concrete. Generally used on building projects and large garden clearances.

Types of waste available for this skip:
o Soil, Concrete, Mixed Domestic, Garden, Light Waste, Mixed Building Waste, Heavy Waste

Waste that cannot be put in a skip:
o TVs/monitors, Plasterboard, Asbestos, Batteries, Tyres, Medical Waste, Flo tubes, Gas cylinders, Electricals, Solvents, Paint tins, Fuels
o Insulation containing asbestos, other insulation containing hazardous substances,other construction materials containing asbestos

The 12 Yard Skip is ideal for large projects, office clearances and general fit outs. Suitable for light bulky waste.

Types of waste available for this skip:
o Light Building, Mixed waste, General Waste, Light Waste, Packaging, Plastic, Cardboard/Paper, Mixed Domestic Heavy Waste

Waste that cannot be put in a skip:
o Rubble, Soil, Concrete,TVs/monitors, Plasterboard, Asbestos, Batteries, Tyres, Medical Waste, Flo tubes, Gas cylinders, Electricals, Solvents, Paint tins, Fuels
o Insulation containing asbestos, other insulation containing hazardous substances,other construction materials containing asbestos

The 16 yard skips are ideal for light building projects, large household jobs, shopfitters as well as other types of general waste.

Types of waste available for this skip:
o Removing large amounts of light, bulky waste, paper or cardboard, furniture, packaging, shop refurbishing jobs with a lot of wood, plastic and metal to remove.

Waste that cannot be put in a skip:
o Rubble, Soil, Concrete, TVs/monitors, Plasterboard, Asbestos, Batteries, Tyres, Medical Waste, Flo tubes, Gas cylinders, Electricals, Solvents, Paint tins, Fuels
o Insulation containing asbestos, other insulation containing hazardous substances, other construction materials containing asbestos.
